    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Great chance to grab an affordable car with plenty of life left for the right buyer. It\u2019s not a showroom piece, but it starts, drives, and could make a solid budget runaround, first project, or handy backup vehicle. If you\u2019re looking for inexpensive wheels and don\u2019t mind a bit of TLC, this one could be a really worthwhile find.",
      "price": 6800.0,
      "reputation": 0.9,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 18
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Mechanically honest and priced for someone who knows what they\u2019re looking at, this car is a solid budget-friendly project with good bones and plenty of upside. The powertrain pulls through the rev range, the chassis feels fundamentally intact, and it has the kind of straightforward, serviceable character that makes it appealing as a fixer, commuter, or parts-saving candidate. Cosmetic wear and age-related flaws are present, but the core package still offers usable performance and a platform worth preserving. If you want an affordable entry point with real potential, this one makes a compelling case.",
      "price": 6800.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 18
    },
    {
